<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module has NONE. The value types (License, the LicenseCategory enum) are immutable, the policy
    and the artifact return their own fields or immutable copies, and the typed exception copies its list
    via List.copyOf — so the representation-exposure detectors (EI_EXPOSE_REP / EI_EXPOSE_REP2) stay quiet
    without any suppression. The filter is kept (empty) so a future, genuinely-reviewed suppression has a
    home with a reason, rather than being added inline. (Distinct from the license allow-list under
    config/license/ — that governs third-party licenses; this one would suppress SpotBugs findings in
    first-party code. Both follow the same reviewed-with-a-reason discipline.)
  -->
</FindBugsFilter>
